events.title: IoT Stammtisch München
events.description: The Eclipse IoT enthusiasts will get together, discuss, enjoy and have a good time! If you are not an enthisiast yet, you are invited as well! Please register - we need to keep track.

events.title: Eclipse Special Day at Jax 2014
events.description: Als Java-Entwicklungsumgebung startete Eclipse einst seine phänomenale Karriere, als Werkbank und Integrationsplattform zahlreicher weiterer Tools für den globalen und teambasierten Entwicklungsprozess hat sich Eclipse längst etabliert. Jenseits der Toolorientierung hat sich Eclipse als Plattform für eine Fülle an Anwendungen einen Namen gemacht. Eclipse ist auch ein wichtiger Innovationstreiber, das zeigen nicht zuletzt Projekte wie Orion oder die enge Verknüpfung mit JavaFX. Der Eclipse Day der JAX 2014 gibt einen Ein- und Überblick in die vielfältigen Aspekte von Eclipse als Anwendungs- und Technologie-Plattform.
events.keywords: Java, JAX 2014, developer conference, Eclipse Special day

events.title: Eclipse Day Sydney
events.description: Eclipse Developer Day Sydney 2014

events.title: Stammtisch Braunschweig
events.description:
The first BREDEX Eclipse event of the year is a Stammtisch on 6th March at 7pm.
The topic for the evening is JavaFX. JavaFX is a modern alternative to Swing, and can be used in desktop and in mobile applications due to its support of touch and gestures.
The first part of the evening will consist of a talk about JavaFX: the technology, examples, first experiences from current projects and thoughts on design and automated testing.
After the talk, we'll go to a local restaurant to get some food and drink and chat about the talk and other Eclipse topics.
Registration is free : please send a short email to eclipsestammtisch@bredex.de if you would like to come.

events.title: OpenUp Camp Nuremberg
events.description:
A unique weekend to discuss the Future of Open. Will cover Open Source, Super Communities and many more topics.
The Eclipse Foundations's Gael Blondelle will present the PolarSys Working Group.

events.title: ERTS - Embedded Real Time Software and Systems
events.description:
The ERTS-2 Congress is a unique European cross sector event on Embedded Software and Systems, a platform for top-level scientific with representatives from universities, research centers and industries. The previous editions gathered more than 100 talks, 500 participants and 60 exhibitors.
This year, Eclipse's Mike Milinkovich will give one of the keynotes, and the PolarSys team will have a booth at ERTS.

events.title: Building OSGi / Maven Applications with Tycho / Maven - The Netherlands
events.description: The Building OSGi and RCP applications with Maven / Tycho training will teach you how to build bundles, features, products, p2 repositories, ... in a fully automated way using Tycho, a Maven-based build system from the Eclipse ecosystem.

events.title: Developing OSGi Equinox - The Netherlands
events.description: This intensive course covers fundamentals of OSGi as well as intermediate topics and specific features of Eclipse Equinox. You will apply the theoretical knowledge in several labs which will give you the practical experience necessary for your projects.

events.title: Eclipse 4 RCP Development - Belgium
events.description: The course will help you understand how to implement your own application based on the Eclipse 4 platform. The Eclipse 4 release significantly changes the programming model for Eclipse RCP development. The course explains the existing core frameworks in Eclipse, e.g. SWT, databinding, plug-in architecture, extension point, etc. as well as the new Eclipse 4 platform concepts, e.g. dependency injection, declarative styling, service consumption, the application model, the rendering framework, etc.

events.title: Eclipse 4 RCP Development - The Netherlands
events.description: The course will help you understand how to implement your own application based on the Eclipse 4 platform. events.title: Eclipse Day Florence
events.description: A one day conference, with a great international scope, dedicated to the diffusion of the Open Source with special focus on Eclipse technologies. Lots of very interesting talks on the most important projects of the Eclipse community and concrete examples of successful adoption of these technologies
